"false" hidden="false" required="false" QuerySchemas="" QueryLocationRoots="" Title="" Values=""/><FullText type="boolean" label="Check for text body to use the full width of the page." readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">false</FullText><TopText type="boolean" label="Check to put text body above Highlighted News" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">false</TopText><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Optional Content" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Height=""><![CDATA[<p><br />Continuing Education credit classes are designed for off track students &amp; community patrons.</p>
<h4><a href="x24821.xml">EVENING SCHOOL</a></h4>
<p>Evening School classes are offered during Fall, Winter, &amp; Spring semesters, and are available for those who are:</p>
<ul>
<li>A current off-track student</li>
<li>A community patron who has completed the Continuing Education application at <a href="http://www.besmart.com">www.besmart.com</a>.</li>
</ul>
<ul></ul>
<h4><a href="x24822.xml">SUMMER SESSION</a></h4>
<ul>
<li>Summer Session is July 28th - September 5th, 2014.</li>
<li>All students currently attending BYU-Idaho and seeking to graduate sooner. It is especially helpful for Spring/Fall track students.</li>
<li>Summer Session is NOT an option for new freshmen prior to their assigned track. You must have completed a minimum of one semester on campus to be eligible.</li>
</ul>
<h4><a href="x24820.xml">CHRISTMAS CLASSES</a></h4>
<ul>
<li>Christmas Classes are a great way to earn up to two credits during your Winter Break</li>
<li>Christmas Classes are offered during the Christmas break. Class dates for 2014 are December 20, 22, 23, 24, 27, 29, 30, 31 &amp; Jan. 3.</li>
</ul>
<p>Click <a class="intLink" href="x37190.xml" title="Admission Requirements">here</a> to learn about Continuing Education admission requirements.</p>
